  "body": "**Suggestion:** \r\n\r\nadd optional field `txtrace`\r\n```\r\n\"Berlin\" : [\r\n                {\r\n                    \"hash\" : \"0x5dc53b4abee831ead995ad46451d3692f102d1f6bae2744dc596c112b8bdba2d\",\r\n                    \"indexes\" : ---\r\n                    \"logs\" : \"0x1dcc4de8dec75d7aab85b567b6ccd41ad312451b948a7413f0a142fd40d49347\",\r\n                    \"txbytes\" : ---\r\n                    \"txtrace\" : \"0x60356035606060606086620186f16160205060555050\"\r\n                },\r\n```\r\n\r\n`txtrace` that represents vm instructions log. \r\n\r\n**why**\r\n\r\nwith this field information we can query all existing tests if they ever executed an opcode1 folloved by opcode2 and so on. \r\n\r\n**downside**\r\n\r\nthis process takes a long time to generate the test, gathering vmtrace information from geth t8n\r\nincrease overall tests size with this debug information that can be obtained on the fly by regenerating the test",
